    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> If you know you want the Linux colours, the easiest thing may be to pass that explicitly, rather than instantiating an InteractiveShell to get it.\n\nI think the intent of the code of ipdbplugin is to set the colors consistently with the IPython config (i.e. ~/.ipython/profile_default/ipython_config.py in my case). Would this be a more robust way to get the IPython colors from the config?\n\n``` python\nfrom IPython.terminal.ipapp import TerminalIPythonApp\ncolors = TerminalIPythonApp.instance().shell.colors\n```\n\nBetter suggestions welcome, obviously !\n"
